author: Jennifer Crothers
title: EastEnders fans notice something wrong with Louise Mitchell's St Patrick's Day text
text:
EastEnders fans notice something wrong with Louise Mitchell's St Patrick's Day text The message between bullies Louise and Madison wasn't quite right... Share Louise's phone showed the wrong date (Photo: BBC) Share Get soaps updates directly to your inbox + Subscribe Thank you for subscribing! Could not subscribe, try again later Invalid Email 
EastEnders viewers got themselves in a flap when they noticed the smallest of mistakes during a dramatic storyline. 
Alexandra (Sydney Craven) and Madison (Seraphina Beh) brutally assaulted Bex in the toilet after they overheard Bex tell Louise she wasn't a good friend for hanging out with them in Friday night's episode. 
The pair then targeted Bex in the horrid attack, pinning her down and writing 'dirty' on her forehead in the girl's bathroom with Louise (Tilly Keeper) on lookout. Read More Madison and Louise were summoned to the head's office (Photo: BBC) Madison sent a text to Louise to warn her to not say a word (Photo: BBC) The date on Louise's phone was a month behind (Photo: BBC) 
Previously, Alexandra and Madison had told a boy Bex sleeps with anyone, following her 'leaked photo' ordeal with former boyfriend Shakil. 
So far, fairly perilous stuff. But some nosy viewers, forgetting the show is a fictional set up, got worked up because of an error over the date. 
Louise and Madison were waiting outside the head's office for a telling off, and Madison texted Louise saying: "Remember, say nothing." 
A close up shot of Louise's phone revealed - for anyone keen on screen-grabbing or pausing live TV - that the date was listed as Friday 17 February, and not Friday 17 March. You would absolutely do what Madison says, wrong day and all (Photo: BBC) Louise: Just as puzzled as everyone else (Photo: BBC) Video Loading Click to play Tap to play The video will start in 8 Cancel Play now
